## Phases and tasks

### Phase 1 â€” Foundation and infra

- [ ] Choose tech stack (backend, DBs, front-end) and document in project
- [ ] Repository structure (monorepo or multi-repo) and Docker Compose layout
- [ ] Docker Compose: all services + Redis + DBs + named volumes for Users, Messages, Notification DBs
- [ ] Single `docker compose up` runs full stack; data persists across stop/start

### Phase 2 â€” Auth and gateway

- [ ] Auth Service: register, login, JWT issuance; Users DB (id, username, email, passwordHash)
- [ ] API Gateway: single entry point; route `/auth/*` to Auth Service; validate JWT on protected routes; proxy `/ws` to Load Balancer
- [ ] Client: login/register flow; store JWT; use for subsequent requests

### Phase 3 â€” WebSocket and presence

- [ ] Load Balancer (e.g. Nginx): distribute WebSocket connections to Channel Services (no sticky sessions)
- [ ] Channel Service: WebSocket server; validate JWT on upgrade (`?token=...`); associate connection with userId
- [ ] Presence Service: register, unregister, heartbeat (batched); sole owner of Presence Redis; TTL 30s
- [ ] Channel Service: on connect â†’ POST /presence/register; on disconnect â†’ POST /presence/unregister; heartbeat every 15s (batched)

### Phase 4 â€” Messaging (send and persist)

- [ ] Messaging Service: receive "send message" from Channel Service
- [ ] Push to Message Queue (with retry); call Presence Service (retry + circuit breaker; fallback: assume offline)
- [ ] If online: publish to Redis Pub/Sub (`recipientIds`, message, issuer, sentAt, channelId)
- [ ] If offline: push to Notification Queue (`recipientId`, issuer, messagePreview)
- [ ] Messaging Processor Worker: consume Message Queue â†’ write to Messages DB
- [ ] Channel Services: subscribe to Pub/Sub; deliver to local connections for `recipientIds`

### Phase 5 â€” Notifications and history

- [ ] Notification Service: consume Notification Queue; call Auth Service for email; send email; write to Notification DB
- [ ] Messaging Service: GET /messages/:channelId â†’ query Messages DB; API Gateway routes history requests here
- [ ] Client: fetch history via HTTP when opening a conversation; real-time via WebSocket

### Phase 6 â€” Resilience (main)

- [ ] Retry with exponential backoff + jitter on: Messagingâ†’Presence, Notificationâ†’Auth, Channelâ†’Presence
- [ ] Circuit breaker on Messagingâ†’Presence; fallback: assume offline, push to Notification Queue

### Phase 7 â€” Polish and bonus (later)

- [ ] Friends/contacts (if in scope): Users DB + GET /users/friends; Gateway route
- [ ] Conversation creation: implicit on first message; return conversationId for history and subsequent messages
- [ ] **(Bonus)** Outbox pattern: Messaging Service writes to outbox table in Messages DB; Outbox Publisher polls â†’ Message Queue + Pub/Sub
- [ ] **(Bonus)** Inbox pattern: Messaging Processor Worker tracks processed message IDs; idempotent consumption

